properties.Name: InternationalStatisticalClassificationOfDiseaseCode
properties.Description:
The International Statistical Classification of Diseases and Related Health Problems (most commonly known by the abbreviation ICD) provides codes to classify diseases and a wide variety of signs, symptoms, abnormal findings, complaints, social circumstances and external causes of injury or disease. Every health condition can be assigned to a unique category and given a code, up to six characters long. Such categories can include a set of similar diseases.

The ICD is a core classification of the WHO Family of International Classifications (WHO-FIC).

The United States will begin official use of ICD-10 on October 10, 2013

Columns.Name: IcdVersionNumber
Columns.Description: The version number of the ICD Code.

Columns.Name: IcdDiseaseCode
Columns.Description: The code identifying an ICD-defined disease.

Columns.Name: IcdDiseaseName
Columns.Description: The name of an ICD-defined disease.

Columns.Name: IcdDiseaseCategoryVersionNumber
Columns.Description: The version of the ICD Disease Code.

Columns.Name: IcdDiseaseCategoryId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an ICD Disease Category.

Columns.Name: MajorDiagnosticCategoryId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Major Diagnostic Category.
